<item>
            <title>[LU-5681] sanity test_56w: falling back to rsync-based migration</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5681</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for Nathaniel Clark &amp;lt;nathaniel.l.clark@intel.com&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run: &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/5097ddda-4606-11e4-b520-5254006e85c2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/5097ddda-4606-11e4-b520-5254006e85c2&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The sub-test test_56w failed with the following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;/mnt/lustre/d56w.sanityw/file2: write failed on volatile for /mnt/lustre/d56w.sanityw/file2 (No such file or directory)
error: migrate: migrate stripe file &apos;/mnt/lustre/d56w.sanityw/file2&apos; failed
falling back to rsync-based migration
mktemp: failed to create file via template `/mnt/lustre/d56w.sanityw/file2.tmp.XXXXXX&apos;: Cannot send after transport endpoint shutdown
 sanity test_56w: @@@@@@ FAIL: /usr/bin/lfs find -stripe_count 8 -type f /mnt/lustre/d56w.sanityw |
         /usr/bin/lfs_migrate -y -c 7 failed 
failed: not a regular file, skipped
failed: not a regular file, skipped
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please provide additional information about the failure here.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Info required for matching: sanity 56w&lt;/p&gt;</description>
